description:
&lt;p&gt;Be part of something special by joining our Neuroscience Team at the Norfolk and Norwich University Hospital (NNUH) as our clinical Educator. We are an innovative and dynamic specialty caring for all age stroke and Patients with Neurological conditions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Education and supporting a team is Key to a successful and competent team which would be led by the successful candidate, This post would also support external agencies ( eg: Ambulance service) with educational programmes’ in enhancing care and education to support our patients journey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As post holder, you will work clinically with a range of learners in the workplace such as overseas, return to practice, supervised practice, pre and post registration programmes across all bands. You will be expected to work with the team, acting as a role model in practice and supporting the team in developing, expanding and consolidating their knowledge within the Neuroscience speciality.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full nights are unlikely but weekends and full day shifts would be likely over a varying number of days which could be discussed at interview.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Full time: &lt;/strong&gt;37.5 hours per week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Open for applications: &lt;/strong&gt;4th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Close for applications: &lt;/strong&gt;10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span&gt; Week commencing 16th November 2020&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rebecca Mitchell - Heydon Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01603 286286&lt;/p&gt;
